content: I'm planning a trip to Japan in March for the Cherry Blossom season and I'm trying to finalize my accommodations. Can you help me decide between a hostel in Shinjuku for $30 a night or an Airbnb in Harajuku for $50 a night? By the way, I was just thinking that if I were to drive from LA to Santa Barbara, it'd take around 2.5 hours, which is pretty reasonable considering the average speed of a car on a highway is around 40 miles per hour.
